article.headline: Detroit 58, Aquinas 48
article.story: DETROIT -- Thomas Kennedy had 17 points to lift Detroit to a 58-48 win over Aquinas on Wednesday night. Woody Payne added 14 points, seven assists and six rebounds for the Titans (3-6) and Michael Harrington had 12 rebounds. Pedja Lazic led Aquinas(4-7) with 21 points and pulled down seven rebounds. Damacious White added 10 points, five rebounds and four assists. Detroit led 26-23 at halftime and extended its advantage to as many as 12 on Jason Bennett's hook shot with 6:18 left that made it 45-33. Aquinas jumped out to a 9-4 lead with 14:25 left in the first half but Tryl Hartfield's 3-pointer gave the Titans a 16-15 lead with 7:21 remaining in the opening half.
